@startuml architecture
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #fafafa
skinparam componentBackgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 15
skinparam packageFontSize 17
skinparam packageFontStyle bold
skinparam noteFontSize 13
skinparam nodesep 40
skinparam ranksep 80
skinparam padding 8

title AgentAid — System Architecture

' Stacked view. Layers stack top-to-bottom; data flows upward
' (agent → SDK → server → frontend). Intra-layer wiring lives in
' the per-layer diagrams:
'   • docs/diagrams/agent-sdk-layer.png
'   • docs/diagrams/server-layer.png
'   • docs/diagrams/frontend-layer.png

' ─────────────────────────── TOP: Frontend Layer ──────────────────────────
package "Frontend Layer" #f3fff3 {
  [Routes (React Router)\n\n• / — drift home\n• /runs/:id — trace detail (Gantt)\n• /compare — run comparison\n• /drift/:signal × 4\n• /evals · /datasets · /runs] as Routes
  [React 19 + Vite + TS\n\n• strict TypeScript\n• fast HMR for dashboard iteration\n• one component per route\n• holds page state + layout] as Components
  [TanStack Query\n\n• typed REST hooks per endpoint\n• polled refresh + cache + retry\n• decodes JSON → typed models] as Query
  [Recharts\n\n• drift time-series (line)\n• score-delta bars\n• tool-call PSI charts] as Charts

  ' Intra-layer flow (read left → right):
  '   1. React Router mounts the Component that matches the URL.
  '   2. The Component calls a typed TanStack Query hook.
  '   3. The Component hands the fetched data to Recharts.
  '   Query → REST API is the seam crossing into the Server tier.
  Routes     -right-> Components : route\nmounts
  Components -right-> Query      : useQuery(...)
  Query      -right-> Charts     : data → render
}

' ───────────── MIDDLE: Server Layer  (FastAPI + SQLModel async) ──────────
package "Server Layer  (FastAPI + SQLModel async)" #fff5e8 {
  [Ingest  /ingest\n\n• accepts span batches from any SDK\n• writes Run + Span rows\n• schedules background eval tasks] as Ingest
  [Eval Orchestrator (modes 1 + 3)\n\n• Mode 1: LLM-judge per terminated run\n• Mode 3: trace-invariant checks\n• writes typed EvalResult] as EvalOrch
  [Regression Driver (mode 2)\n\n• replays golden dataset against\n  current prompt + model\n• writes RegressionRun row per pass] as RegOrch
  [Drift Workers\n\n• 5 s tick over recent DB rows\n• ADWIN — quality (judge scores)\n• MMD — input (query embeddings)\n• PSI — tool-call frequencies per role\n• PSI — citation-weight attribution\n• writes DriftStateRow per signal] as Drift
  database "SQLite\n\n• runs, spans, evals,\n  drift state\n• append-only span store" as DB
  [REST API\n\n• /runs · /evals · /drift\n• /datasets · /regressions · /compare\n• typed read-mostly views of DB] as Api

  ' Force one horizontal row inside the server layer
  Ingest   -[hidden]right- EvalOrch
  EvalOrch -[hidden]right- RegOrch
  RegOrch  -[hidden]right- Drift
  Drift    -[hidden]right- DB
  DB       -[hidden]right- Api
}

' ─────────────────── BOTTOM: Agent + SDK Layer ───────────────────────────
package "Agent + SDK Layer" #f4f8ff {
  [Reference Agent\n\n• Pydantic AI — typed agent + tools, async\n• planner + worker — supervisor dispatches\n  one worker subagent per paper\n• multi-modal vision — figures sent as\n  base64 JPEGs to the model\n• mock arXiv default — offline corpus;\n  real arXiv via env flag] as Agent
  component "agentaid SDK (Python + TypeScript)\n\n• OTel/GenAI emitter — gen_ai.* +\n  agentaid.* span attributes\n• Python + TS parity — same wire format,\n  one server contract" as Sdk
  [Bare Anthropic SDK Example\n\n• same OTel/GenAI wire, no framework\n  — proves the platform is\n  framework-agnostic] as Bare

  ' Force one horizontal row inside the agent layer
  Agent -[hidden]right- Sdk
  Sdk   -[hidden]right- Bare
}

' ─────────────────── Cross-layer seams (the stack joints) ────────────────
' Only the cross-layer arrows are drawn at the master level. The intra-layer
' wiring (Ingest → DB, Drift → DB, etc.) is shown in server-layer.puml.
Query -down-> Api  : typed REST client\n(GET /runs · /evals\n /drift · /compare · …)
Sdk -up->   Ingest : HTTP POST /ingest\n{spans: [ … ]}

note bottom of Sdk
  Regression mode (mode 2) loops the
  reference agent through the same
  /ingest path as production traffic.
end note

@enduml
